# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# This file is NOT loaded by Vite — documentation only.
# Vite reads `.env.development`, `.env.local`, etc. — never ".env.example".
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# Client (this folder):
#   - `.env.development` can set VITE_API_URL (committed in this repo for convenience).
#   - Copy `.env.local.example` → `.env.local` to point at your droplet when you are not running uvicorn locally.
#   - Optional: `VITE_API_KEY` = same as DASHBOARD_API_KEY on the server (scripts / CI only).
#
# You sign in through the UI; password is NOT stored in env on the client.
#
# Droplet `/home/mason/agent/.env` must include at least:
#   SESSION_SECRET=<random long string; e.g. openssl rand -hex 32>
#   DASHBOARD_PASSWORD=<strong password you type in the dashboard>
#   DASHBOARD_CORS_ORIGINS=https://YOURUSER.github.io,http://localhost:5173,http://127.0.0.1:5173
#
# GitHub Pages is HTTPS: the API must be HTTPS too or the browser blocks requests (mixed content).
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
